                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13631415" author="iamaleksey" created="Sun, 14 Apr 2013 23:06:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5352&quot; title=&quot;PreparedStatements get mixed up between Keyspaces&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5352&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5352&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; caused this. QueryProcessor.storePreparedStatement() handles keyspace==null case, but it&apos;ll never get to this point, because ClientState.getKeyspace() call in prepare() will throw when keyspace==null. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached trivial fix replaces getKeyspace() call with getRawKeyspace(), that will return null without throwing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13632141" author="pchalamet" created="Mon, 15 Apr 2013 20:33:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;works for me. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
